c:["$","ul",null,{"children":[["$","li",null,{"children":"Pre-shift inspections before each use"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Periodic inspections during the rental period"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Ensuring the operator is qualified"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Ensuring a competent person is available on site"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Safe operation, rigging, and signal person requirements"}]]}]
d:["$","h3",null,{"children":"Operated Rental (Equipment + Operator)"}]
e:["$","p",null,{"children":"The rental company provides both the crane and the operator (and potentially additional crew). In this arrangement, the rental company retains more control — and more responsibility:"}]
f:["$","ul",null,{"children":[["$","li",null,{"children":"The rental company is responsible for operator qualification and certification"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"Pre-shift inspections are typically the operator's (and therefore the rental company's) responsibility"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"The rental company must ensure the crane is maintained and inspected per OSHA standards"}],["$","li",null,{"children":"The contractor still has site safety obligations as the controlling employer"}]]}]
10:["$","h2",null,{"children":"The Annual Inspection Question"}]
11:["$","p",null,{"children":["Here's where it gets contentious: ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"who is responsible for the annual comprehensive inspection on a rented crane?"}]]}]
12:["$","p",null,{"children":"Under OSHA 1926.1412(c), the employer must ensure that each crane receives an annual comprehensive inspection by a qualified person. For rented equipment:"}]
13:["$","ul",null,{"children":[["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"The rental company"}]," typically performs the annual inspection as part of their fleet maintenance program — they own the equipment and control its lifecycle."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"The contractor"}]," must verify that a current annual inspection exists before using the crane. \"We assumed the rental company handled it\" is not a defense."]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"The rental agreement"}]," should specify who is responsible. If it doesn't, both parties are exposed."]}]]}]
14:["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Best practice:"}]," Before accepting delivery of any rented crane, request a copy of the most recent annual inspection report. Verify it's within 12 months. File it with your project records. If the rental company can't provide one, don't accept the crane."]}]
15:["$","h2",null,{"children":"OSHA's Multi-Employer Worksite Doctrine"}]
16:["$","p",null,{"children":"OSHA can cite multiple employers for the same hazard on a multi-employer worksite. Under OSHA's Multi-Employer Citation Policy (CPL 02-00-124), employers are classified as:"}]
17:["$","ul",null,{"children":[["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Creating employer:"}]," The employer whose actions created the hazard (e.g., a rental company sending out a crane with a known deficiency)"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Exposing employer:"}]," The employer whose employees are exposed to the hazard (e.g., the contractor whose workers are in the crane's operating radius)"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Correcting employer:"}]," The employer responsible for correcting the hazard (could be either party depending on the rental agreement)"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Controlling employer:"}]," The employer with general supervisory authority over the worksite (typically the GC)"]}]]}]
18:["$","p",null,{"children":["The practical impact: ",["$","strong",null,{"children":"both the rental company and the contractor can be cited for an uninspected crane."}]," The rental company as the creating employer (they provided the equipment without proper inspection), and the contractor as the exposing employer (they used it without verifying)."]}]
19:["$","h2",null,{"children":"What to Include in Your Rental Agreement"}]
1a:["$","p",null,{"children":"A well-drafted crane rental agreement should address every inspection and maintenance obligation explicitly. At minimum:"}]
1b:["$","ul",null,{"children":[["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Annual inspection responsibility:"}]," Who performs it, who pays for it, documentation requirements"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Pre-delivery inspection:"}]," Rental company certifies the crane passed inspection before delivery"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Maintenance during rental:"}]," Who handles preventive and corrective maintenance during the rental period"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Deficiency reporting:"}]," Contractor's obligation to report deficiencies discovered during use; rental company's obligation to respond"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Documentation sharing:"}]," Rental company provides copies of annual inspection, maintenance records, and safety device certifications"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Return condition requirements:"}]," What condition must the crane be in upon return; who pays for damage"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Operator qualifications (if operated rental):"}]," Rental company provides certification documentation for their operator"]}]]}]
1c:["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pre-Delivery Checklist for Contractors"}]
1d:["$","p",null,{"children":"Before putting a rented crane to work, your competent person should verify:"}]
1e:["$","ol",null,{"children":[["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Current annual inspection:"}]," Dated within the last 12 months, performed by a qualified person, with documented results"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Load chart:"}]," Present in the cab, legible, and matching the crane's current configuration (boom length, counterweight, etc.)"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Operator manual:"}]," Present and accessible in the cab"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Safety devices:"}]," All functioning — anti-two-block, LMI/LCI, boom stops, swing stops (as applicable)"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Wire rope condition:"}]," Visual check, no removal criteria met per 1926.1413"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Hydraulic system:"}]," No visible leaks, proper fluid levels"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Structural condition:"}]," No visible cracks, deformation, or corrosion"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Outriggers/stabilizers:"}]," Functioning properly, pads available"]}],["$","li",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Certificate of insurance:"}]," Rental company's liability coverage documentation"]}]]}]
1f:["$","p",null,{"children":"Document this pre-delivery inspection with date, time, the person who performed it, and the results. If deficiencies are found, document them and notify the rental company immediately — in writing."}]
20:["$","h2",null,{"children":"Common Disputes and How to Avoid Them"}]
21:["$","h3",null,{"children":"1. \"The Crane Arrived With a Problem\""}]
22:["$","p",null,{"children":"Without a documented pre-delivery inspection, the rental company will claim the problem occurred during your use. With a documented inspection showing the deficiency existed on arrival, you have evidence. Always inspect on arrival and document everything — photos, written notes, timestamps."}]
23:["$","h3",null,{"children":"2. \"We Didn't Know the Annual Was Overdue\""}]
24:["$","p",null,{"children":"OSHA doesn't care who \"should have\" known. If you're using the crane, you're responsible for verifying it's compliant. Request the annual inspection report before or at delivery. Make it a non-negotiable step in your rental process."}]
25:["$","h3",null,{"children":"3. \"Maintenance Is Their Problem\""}]
26:["$","p",null,{"children":"On a bare rental, the contractor often becomes responsible for day-to-day maintenance during the rental period. If a brake fails because no one greased the swing bearing for 6 months of continuous use, \"the rental company should have done it\" won't hold up. Clarify maintenance obligations in the contract and follow through."}]
27:["$","h2",null,{"children":"Protect Both Sides With Documentation"}]
28:["$","p",null,{"children":"Rental crane disputes are documentation disputes. The party with better records wins — in OSHA hearings, in insurance claims, and in court. Both the rental company and the contractor benefit from comprehensive, timestamped, inspection and maintenance documentation that clearly establishes what condition the crane was in at every stage of the rental lifecycle."}]
29:["$","section",null,{"className":"bg-navy py-16 px-4","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4","children":"Document Every Crane — Owned or Rented"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-gray-300 mb-8 max-w-xl mx-auto","children":"CraneCheck manages inspection records for your entire fleet, including rented equipment. Pre-delivery checklists, inspection verification, and complete audit trails."}],["$","$L33",null,{"href":"/pricing","className":"bg-brand hover:bg-brand-dark text-white px-8 py-3 rounded-lg font-semibold transition-colors","children":"Start Free Trial →"}]]}]}]
